social_posts.post_text:
I fell deeply in love with New York City this week. I came here alone last Sunday and left with so many new friends. My heart feels softened by the spirit of this city. The wink and a nod from a kind stranger, just because. The helping hands guiding a lost traveler on the subway. The locals inviting a wanderer to have a seat on their steps on a sunny Saturday afternoon. Endless opportunities for connection. Hazard and delight at every street corner. 

I got a chance to make music with some of the most talented people I’ve ever met. The sessions were egoless and child-like. I let my guard down in a major way and was able to truly COLLABORATE. Each session felt a bit like that food fight scene from the movie Hook: “You’re doing it, PETER!” 

I went to the 911 memorial and cried a solid 2 hours straight. It just hits you differently when you actually get to know what this city is about. 

Ive never felt so accepted and welcomed in my life. I love you forever, NYC.
Grateful for this dude. Might have to give him my fav hat. He just looks so good in it.

I have to throw it back a little bit here. Someone sent me this picture recently and I really needed to see it. 

I’ve been struggling with the notion of rejection lately. Im really close to releasing my music for the first time. And it’s terrifying. Im in this weird purgatory of trying to perfect something because I’m afraid of releasing it and people hating it. And there’s so much coming up emotionally. So many wounds that I never truly dealt with when they were deep cuts. I just kind of ignored them and distracted myself with some form of achievement or whatever. And I’m truly feeling them now. 

Anywho, back to this picture: after my senior year in high school, I had a lot of football recruiting attention, but no scholarship offers. My SR season ended and I received a lot of awards and recognition but no tangible realistic future in football. Oof that was painful. My first real heartbreak. I didn’t know what to do next. In my heart I knew I had more ball to play. But the odds of making it were so low and society can be brutally harsh to those chasing their dreams against all odds. 

I decided to go for it anyways. Just because that was my truth. I went to Harbor JC and played one season. Long story short, 6 months after graduating high school, I wound up at my dream school. UCLA. On a full scholarship. This is my freshman picture from my first fall camp. I was just so excited and grateful. I might have been the only dude to smile this big for his picture. But I couldnt hide it. UCLA was my dream. And I was living it officially. 

I needed to see this picture. Just a really nice reminder that good things happen when you follow your dreams and do the work. And I’m doing both. Always have. Always will. Rejection happens but it hasn’t killed me yet. Thanks for reading. GO BRUINS!

I’m so grateful for you. And I just wanted to express that and share a tad bit of my story. 

IN MY LANE releases everywhere digitally at MIDNIGHT! 

All love. Thank you. 

#newmusic #indieartist #gratitude

IN MY LANE is out EVERYWHERE digitally! 

This is the first song I ever made. I wrote, composed, arranged, produced, performed, and (partially) mixed this myself. This is truly my music and I’m so grateful to share it with you. 

I want to thank you for your support and love. If you’re reading this, I love you and I pray for nothing but the best for you. 

I want to send a special thank you for to my boy @soal.music. There’s no way I could have ever started this song without you. 

And another special thank you to my mentor and fellow “lefty” @crclarts. There’s no way I could have ever finished this without you. 

And one final thank you to my friend @ohhpatches for bringing it on the drums and really finalizing the sound I wanted for this tune. You crushed it!

🙏🙏❤️❤️🤗🤗⚡️⚡️

Lyric video for IN MY LANE is now out on my YouTube channel. Super stoked how this turned out. 

When I was writing and producing this song out, I kept seeing the color purple whenever I heard that synth pad float through. And orange sunsets. And long open highways. All the pictures from my head are now available to watch. 

Thanks so much for your support. Link to the video is in my bio and my linktree. ❤️

#newmusic #musicvideo #indiepop

I can’t thank you enough. I’ve got lots of music coming your way very soon. In the meantime, salute/salamati/cheers. I’m so grateful for you!

social_posts.post_text:
Bad day to be a beer!

Learned how to use Vegemite. It’s quite nice with butter. Like a salty spread. Not to be used solo in large quantities. 

Took the Great Ocean Road and spent the day in Lorne. I can’t tell you how long it’s been since I have been in the ocean. I get a bit reluctant because it gets tricky on the old prosthetic. Keep it on and get it sandy? Take it off and hop and crawl? I took it off and hopped my one legged ass into the Australian abyss and it was the best decision I’ve made in a long time. 

No kangaroo sighting but we had some bird friends come very close to flex on us.
Had to hit it while here in the motherland. Thanks @debbiekebbell for a great workout and phenomenal tunes!
